<p><q>In <qex>impuberal</qex> animals the cerebellum is, in proportion
to the brain proper, greatly less than in adults.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

